content:
"Who knew feelings were a thing aye? Crazy." Yes indeed! My wife and I can't wait for your EP! 

Two thoughts, and definitely take them or leave them because we've been following you for years now and think your music and comedy are about the most awesome ever! Thought #1: As you continue your journey from "writing songs about dicks," please don't delete your old stuff! It is fantastic and the arc of your musical evolution is so amazing to see and enjoy! Thought #2: If you ever decide to push for serious widespread distribution of this song (which I think you could/should!), changing the lyric of "happy to have called London home" to a general lyric of "happy to have called 'other places' home" (or something similar) will broaden your appeal if you can still sing those lyrics with the same amazing heart and soul... allowing others to sing the lyrics with you with the same heart soul (and thinking of their own homes away from home)... a feeling that resonates in so many, even if we haven't ever lived in London specifically. 

Just my opinion though, totally take it or leave it you. You're the bomb and so is this song... I'll sing it regardless as soon as I can buy the EP. Loving all you are doing!

content:
So youtube's autoplay bullshit that I've turned off a thousand times fucked me out of a long comment....
Basically, Matt, you should start a gaming channel. Three videos a week and the occasional livestream would be more than enough to pay your bills if you can pull in about 20k views a video. Tobuscus is an example of a youtuber who grew their main channel a lot by starting a gaming channel, and then also had their gaming channel be so popular they switched to that basically full time.

Also, you should learn SEO, it will make your channel really noticeable to the types of people you want to notice it. For example, if you made a video of you doing the Star Wars theme song on a kazoo and uploaded it on Wednesday afternoon before the US release of the new Star Wars movie, and then did alright with your SEO you could drive millions of people to your channel to see you kazooing Star Wars, then it's just a matter of setting up a playlist of your stuff that starts with the mild silly stuff and gets a little weirder the further you go. You want to ease people into it so they don't go straight from Star Wars to "When we Kiss." This is an especially powerful way to drive people to your channel now that youtube has come out with their trending tab, capture part of the swell of a major media event, end up on the trending tab and then you can ride the swell for longer thus reaching more potential long term video watchers. It's a dumbed down version of the old front page, but it's definitely going to be effective.

Anyway, after all that, I hope to be able to be a patreon supporter by the end of January, but till then this song applies to me too.
